quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
14,43,"when they shall keep pressing ahead in haste, their heads lifted up, their gaze directed forward, {1} unable to look away from what they behold, their hearts utterly void.",footnotes:1:This graphic picture depicts the horrible plight of the wrongdoers on the Day of Reckoning. When they will realize the situation
14,44,"(O Muhammad), warn mankind of the Day when a severe chastisement shall overtake them, and the wrong-doers will say: "Our Lord, grant us respite for a short while; we shall respond to Your call and will follow Your Messengers." (But they will be clearly told): "Are you not the same who swore earlier that they shall never suffer decline?""
14,45,"You said so even though you had lived in the dwellings of those who had wronged themselves (by sinning), and you were aware how We dealt with them, and We had even explained to you all this by giving examples."
14,46,"Indeed the unbelievers contrived their plan, but it is in Allah's power to nullify their plan, even though their plans were such that would move even mountains. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
14,47,"So, do not think, (O Prophet), that Allah will go back upon His promise to His Messengers. {1} Surely Allah is Mighty, Lord of retribution.",footnotes:1:Though this has been addressed to the Prophet (peace be upon him)
14,48,"(Do warn them of the) Day when the heavens and the earth shall be altogether changed; {1} when all will appear fully exposed before Allah, the One, the Irresistible!",footnotes:1:It is obvious from this verse and some hints in the Quran that on the occasion of Resurrection
14,49,"On that Day you shall see the guilty ones secured in chains;"
14,50,"their garments shall be black {1} as if made out of pitch, and flames of the Fire shall cover their faces",footnotes:1:Some commentators and translators are of the opinion that Qatiran stands for sulphur or molten copper but actually it stands for tar and the like.
14,51,"so that Allah may requite each person for his deeds. Allah is swift in reckoning."
14,52,"This is a proclamation for all mankind that they may be warned by it, and that they may know that their God is none but the One True God, and that men of understanding may take heed."
